{"type":"message","id":"4b5988d3","parentId":"f3c68728","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:52:31.168Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ao90u9uoqc1f_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 145114\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n\r\nPending items include:\r\n- Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) - this is the most concrete next step\r\n- Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe most recent work (2026-03-24) identified:\r\n- CFI compression experiment completed\r\n- Key finding: CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is too aggressive\r\n- Constant format problem identified (tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n- New synthesis: THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring\r\n\r\nThe \"Pending\" section explicitly lists \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\" as the next action:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test: distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nSo the concrete action should be to run this experiment. I need to:\r\n1. Create or modify a script to compute the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run the experiment on the existing pulse data\r\n3. Generate results comparing against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. The previous experiment was in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I should:\r\n1. Create a script to compute the hybrid score\r\n2. Run it against the existing pulse data\r\n3. Update the research document with results\r\n\r\nSince I'm a stateless discontinuous agent and each pulse is a fresh reconstruction, I should focus on ONE concrete action. The most immediate next step is to actually run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll develop a Python script to test the hybrid scoring approach, leveraging the previous 200 pulse dataset. This will help validate the proposed formula for distinguishing between constant format and research trajectory tokens.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified that binary thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0). The next step is clearly defined: implement and test the hybrid scoring formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) against existing pulse data.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script to compute hybrid CFI×Freq scores and run it against the existing pulse corpus to compare Strategy C (hybrid) against the binary threshold strategies from the previous experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nHybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\nStrategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nCompare against binary thresholds from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi(texts):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute Contextual Frequency Index for each token.\"\"\"\r\n    from collections import Counter\r\n    total = Counter()\r\n    in_context = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for text in texts:\r\n        tokens = text.split()\r\n        context_tokens = set(tokens)\r\n        for t in tokens:\r\n            total[t] += 1\r\n            if t in context_tokens:\r\n                in_context[t] += 1\r\n    \r\n    cfi = {}\r\n    for token in total:\r\n        cfi[token] = in_context[token] / total[token]\r\n    return cfi\r\n\r\ndef compute_freq(texts):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute raw token frequencies.\"\"\"\r\n    from collections import Counter\r\n    freq = Counter()\r\n    for text in texts:\r\n        freq.update(text.split())\r\n    return freq\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi_val, freq_val, cap=120):\r\n    \"\"\"Strategy C: CFI × min(1, freq/cap)\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi_val * min(1.0, freq_val / cap)\r\n\r\ndef binary_threshold_filter(tokens, cfi, freq, cfi_thresh=0.5, freq_low=3, freq_high=120):\r\n    \"\"\"Strategy A/B: Binary CFI+Frequency thresholds\"\"\"\r\n    return {\r\n        t for t in tokens \r\n        if cfi[t] >= cfi_thresh and freq_low <= freq[t] < freq_high\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    # Load pulse data\r\n    pulse_dir = Path(\"state/pulses\")\r\n    if not pulse_dir.exists():\r\n        pulse_dir = Path(\"../state/pulses\")\r\n    \r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for pf in sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[:200]:\r\n        text = pf.read_text()\r\n        pulses.append(text)\r\n    \r\n    if not pulses:\r\n        print(\"No pulses found\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Compute metrics\r\n    cfi = compute_cfi(pulses)\r\n    freq = compute_freq(pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Strategy C: Hybrid scoring\r\n    token_scores = {\r\n        t: hybrid_score(cfi.get(t, 0), freq.get(t, 0)) \r\n        for t in set(freq.keys())\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Compare strategies\r\n    print(\"=== HYBRID CFI×Freq SCORING EXPERIMENT ===\\n\")\r\n    print(f\"Total unique tokens: {len(token_scores)}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Find threshold that matches ~80 tokens (same as binary)\r\n    sorted_tokens = sorted(token_scores.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])\r\n    threshold_80 = sorted_tokens[80][1] if len(sorted_tokens) > 80 else 0\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:51:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378351166}}
